# The Contract üìú

Strongly typed schema defines the API.

```graphql
type User {
  id: ID!
  name: String!
  posts: [Post]
}

type Post {
  title: String
}

type Query {
  me: User
}
```

# Getting Data üì•

Like REST `GET`.

```graphql
query {
  user(id: 1) {
    name
    email
    posts {
      title
    }
  }
}
```
Returns JSON matching the shape of the query.

# Changing Data üì§

Like REST `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE`.

```graphql
mutation {
  createPost(title: "Hello World") {
    id
    title
  }
}
```

# The Logic üß†

Resolvers are functions on the server that fetch the actual data for a field.

```javascript
const resolvers = {
  Query: {
    user: (parent, args) => db.findUser(args.id)
  }
};
```

# Realtime ‚ö°

Maintain a persistent connection to the server (usually WebSockets).

Receive updates instantly when data changes.

```graphql
subscription {
  newPost {
    title
  }
}
```

